prompt: Nighttime school camp hall gone surreal: teens sliding downslope of warped folding chairs, a glass torch-rod humming, a silver vape-smoke fish leaping, walls folding into red-earth crate-labeled stairs descending through years—your glowing-pixel face the only clear one; cinematic lighting, hyper-real, 1.85, Lynchian.

Add a ghost-outline of the viewer stepping out of their body, duplicate offering a pulsing blue vape across the gap while memory-thread reels from breast pocket toward the cracked 00:00 pressure gauge hovering over the yawning dark.
Swap the blank ticket for a pixelated CCTV still, inked rules crawling up the holder’s veins as the EXIT glyph flashes ahead and folding chairs clatter into a corridor toward dawn.

Add a pocket-square paper plane where the thermal sheet was, its creases hiding the CCTV frame; let daylight spill through the silhouette-shaped doorway, cereal-tinted, while a light snowfall of chrome prefect badges drifts across the threshold.
